The paper proposes a novel framework for Visual Question Answering (VQA) in the medical domain that overcomes the labeled data limitation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed framework leverages unsupervised Denoising Auto-Encoder (DAE) and supervised Meta-Learning techniques, which are commonly used in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves natural language processing for VQA, which falls under the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with medical images, which suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
